<DOC><DOCNO> AP890417-0246 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-17-89 1141EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-Earns-PPG     04-17 0223</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Earns-PPG,0230</SECOND><HEAD>Coatings, Chemicals Pace Record First Quarter</HEAD><DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   PPG Industries Inc. said today that highersales and operating earnings in its coatings and chemicalsbusinesses helped produce the company's best first quarter ever,with a 9 percent profit increase.   The company said after-tax earnings rose to $129.8 million, or$1.15 per share, in the first 1989 quarter from $118.6 million, or$1.07 per share, in 1988's first quarter. Sales increased 6 percentto $1.459 billion from $1.373 billion.   Lower sales of flatglass and unfavorable currency transactionswashed out sales gains for original and replacement auto glass, thePittsburgh-based company said.   Sales of glass, PPG's leading product, slid 1.7 percent to $588million from $598 million. Operating earnings for the unit dropped18.3 percent to $94 million from $115 million.   Increased sales of automotive paint and industrial coatings andprogress in controlling costs overcame the less favorable currencyexchange rates in PPG's second-largest line. Unit sales rose 10percent to $512 million from $465 million, and operating earningsrose 17.6 percent to $80 million from $68 million.   Improved prices and sales volume for most basic and specialtychemicals, including a new chemical plant in Taiwan, helped liftthe unit's revenue 40.7 percent to $315 million from $261 millionand boost operating earnings 20.6 percent to $76 million from $63million.</TEXT></DOC>